**<span style="font-size: 12pt;">Currently, railroads and trains are used not for the opportunity they bring to unite individuals but rather as a means for capital accumulation. Social planners seek to produce the most efficient railways possible in a deliberate attempt to create structure amidst the chaos of the many actions of the world. Train graffiti is in opposition to this form of rational planning. It is a moment in time that gives power to those cast aside by the normative structures of politics. Graffiti is a strategy for empowerment without totalizing control.</span>**
